“You say you’ve learned from 2016,” Melcer told them, according to a government official who was present.
Russia’s campaign in the United States demonstrated that fake personas on social media could influence events.
More recently, companies in Israel and elsewhere started using fake personas to spread messages on behalf of political parties and their allies.
An early proponent of modernizing Israel’s election laws was Tehilla Shwartz Altshuler, a law professor and senior researcher with the nonpartisan Israel Democracy Institute.
All but one of Israel’s political parties said they would accept the proposed restrictions.